ICYMI: Our Universal Render Pipeline 3D Sample just dropped in the #Unity Hub! üåü

It includes 4 scenes with different art styles, rendering paths, and complexity you can explore to learn how to use #URP features for accelerated multiplatform development.

Download it here: https://on.unity.com/47CZ1vW

post_text:
For nearly a decade, Gameheads has been fostering game development skills and providing industry experiences for underrepresented youth in Oakland, California with support from the Unity Charitable Fund.

Unity's Jessica Lindl recently spoke with Gameheads partners Kevin Johnson and Trinidad Hermida to explore the ongoing efforts and opportunities aimed at building a more inclusive and diverse games industry.

Listen to the full conversation here:

üéâ Unity Muse is now available in early access.

Get ready to easily explore ideas and iterate faster with powerful AI capabilities like Chat, and Sprite and Texture generation. Subscribe to access and discover an easier way to find answers, produce usable code, and generate project-ready assets that are safe to use thanks to our custom-built, responsibly trained models.

Learn more: on.unity.com/46cBp08

Looking to supercharge your vision? The 2024 #UnityForHumanity Grant is now open! If you have a groundbreaking real-time 3D project or idea that aims to create a world that‚Äôs more equitable, inclusive, or sustainable, then apply now!

But wait - there‚Äôs more! Singer-songwriter and mental health pioneer Jewel will help select a grant recipient with a project that focuses specifically on themes of wellness. Learn more and apply today to make an even bigger difference! https://on.unity.com/3uboRc6

Find full details on Discord: https://on.unity.com/3u5D9Ln

Or on Unity Discussions: https://on.unity.com/3u8MzWs

One of the bigger challenges with preparing future generations to join the workforce of tomorrow, is bridging the gap between education and workforce systems. üí°

From the Unity Workforce Grant to a joint partnership with Google Play and the Indonesian Game Association, hear from VP of Social Impact Jessica Lindl on a few ways Unity is working to tackle these challenges: https://on.unity.com/3Ld5kh0

üéÆ Calling all game devs in Brighton! üåä

Get ready for Unity Developer Days in Brighton, on September 14th. Join us for a day of inspiration, learning, and networking with local indie and AAA talent.

üé§ Listen to talks by Unity experts
ü§ù Network with fellow developers
üìö Share knowledge and insights
üìß Showcase your Unity project

Don't miss this opportunity to connect with the Unity community and level up your game development skills. Secure your spot now https://on.unity.com/3P7XGGV

Looking to dive into the world of multiplayer game development? We've got you covered!

Our reading list includes tutorials, articles, demos, and documentation to help you master the art of building solid and scalable multiplayer infrastructure. With the right resources and a bit of elbow grease, you'll be able to get your idea off the ground.

So what are you waiting for? Dig in: https://on.unity.com/3OVdED3

Have you thought about your game's post-launch experience?

Your game is flying off virtual shelves and players love it, but what about scaling? Server hosting? Analytics?

post_text:
How do you create a compelling and challenging boss fight in a game? ‚öî

In Evil Wizard, you play as a former Final Boss rising from defeat and attempting to reclaim their castle from so-called heroes üòà

We were lucky to have Rubber Duck Games over on our blog for a technical deep dive into how they designed the first boss fight in their game, from prototyping to testing and balancing: https://on.unity.com/3KJYCyM

In the next Dev Blitz Day, ask our Graphics team all your questions about Global Illumination, Shaders, URP, HDRP, and more. Post your questions in the Unity Forum or Discord on May 24, and the team will answer everything on May 25.

More on how it works: https://on.unity.com/45btMaV

post_text:
Are you building a cooperative multiplayer game?

Here is a fantastic 4-part breakdown on how you can use Netcode for GameObjects to build a production-ready multiplayer game: https://on.unity.com/3mglRHJ

üéâ We're thrilled to announce that our short film, Enemies, is nominated for a prestigious Webby Award in the short-form video category!

This recognition places Enemies among the top 12% of the nearly 14,000 projects entered from around the world ü§Ø

We're competing for the Internet's two most coveted awards: The Webby Award and The Webby People's Voice Award. Help us win the People's Voice Award by voting for Enemies here: https://on.unity.com/3UgFXya

post_text:
Using a small but mighty team of five people, Eleven Puzzles was able to put all the pieces of creating a multiplayer, multiplatform game together üß©

How?! They had to tackle scaling, connect players across platforms, fix bugs in less than a day, and more... But the most important part of all? Build a good game.

Read how they used Unity and Unity Gaming Services such as Lobby and Cloud Diagnostics to help move development along without wasting precious time: https://on.unity.com/3JOkbNr

üßë‚Äçüè´ Now, more than ever, we have a responsibility to equip young people with the skills necessary for future jobs ‚Äì providing them with learning that translates to earning. Jessica Lindl, Unity VP of Social Impact, talks about how to game your career with skills like learning Unity.

post_text:
Look, a mysterious lock! There's a glimmer under the rock to your left, could it be a key?

üîë + üîí = üîì

New genre unlocked: Cozy Games üõãÔ∏è

What is a cozy game? Why do players love them so much? Are there cozy assets?! So many questions, so many answers. Grab your favorite warm drink and read more: https://on.unity.com/3whP7PT

We‚Äôve made several updates and improvements to Global Illumination in the latest #Unity 2022.2 Tech Stream release to help you better achieve realistic indirect lighting üîÜ

‚≠ê Improved performance for light baking with Progressive Lightmappers
‚≠ê Changes to path tracing in HDRP
‚≠ê Added features in the Preview release of Adaptive Probe Volumes
‚≠ê Deprecation of Enlighten Baked GI

Get all the details in our blog üîΩ üîΩ

üé§ Unity: What wisdom can you share with people who are graduating from school and interested in mobile game monetization as a career? üé§

üßç‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è Dean: "Having even just a bit of experience with apps previously from college helped me get my foot in the door. It helps if you‚Äôre able to speak a bit of the language when it comes to KPIs and metrics used to measure app performance.

I didn‚Äôt have a lot of experience coming out of school, but I had a baseline understanding of how apps made money. If you‚Äôre interested in it, pursue that curiosity and see where it takes you."

Learn more from Joe Dean, Advertising and Monetization Manager and Unity Growth Master about how to get started in the industry and some of the most effective strategies for approaching monetization in games: https://on.unity.com/3QwsrVc

post_text:
We hope you've had the time to rest and enjoy before the new year ‚ô• ü§ó
And for those who have some gamedev-related resolutions, you're in luck!

We gathered a few of our free courses and projects, spanning all levels, to help you learn some new skills üòâ
Take a look back on our diversity recruitment journey with Kaylynn! ü§©

Happy New Year ü•≥

‚è∞ Our Asset Store New Year Sale is ending soon, don't forget to use coupon code HELLO2023 to save another 20% on purchases of $300 or more ‚Äî before time runs out: https://on.unity.com/3i8TFV0

üéä Looking to kick off the New Year with some fresh mobile marketing insights? Look no further!

Here are some of the top insights and tips on owning and conquering user acquisition from Ekaterina Zueva, Senior User Acquisition Manager at MY.GAMES: https://on.unity.com/3IlK6wQ
üíñ Discover Unity's growing Employee Resource Groups and learn how they are fostering a more inclusive workplace.

‚ú® We‚Äôve always believed in the power of our creators to do extraordinary things. ‚ú® Read more about what we‚Äôre doing to support their efforts to make the world a better place: https://unity.com/esg

Remember Snake.io? üêç

In our latest Growth Masters interview, we sat down with CK Wang, CEO of Kooapps, a leading developer of mobile casual games.

Here, we learn about how he and his team have taken games such as Snake.io to the next level with innovative monetization and user acquisition strategies as well as the tricks he wishes he knew when starting out: https://on.unity.com/3YM5uRL

Join us as we sit down with Jatin Mittal the User Acquisition Team Lead at TapNation as he shares what he's learned in a constantly evolving mobile marketing industry.

Check out his journey, the challenges he's faced, and his approach to strategy: https://on.unity.com/3HPUgWc

How do you build a community for your game as an indie dev? üôã‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è

Aka, a wholesome game with a distinct watercolor painting look, had been grabbing attention online. Namra, the lead developer, shared some advice for developers just starting out and looking to get their game noticed üí°

üë• When choosing a channel to build your community: choose one where you can connect with other people from the profession, like game developers or even publishers

üé• Don‚Äôt be shy and share some content and progress: animated GIFs or videos that really represent your game.

‚ú® It‚Äôs better to post a little bit less, maybe once a week, but post something that‚Äôs really good, rather than post a lot.

üëã Taking advantage of hashtags like #gamedev and #indiegames can help with visibility and will have you more inclined to meet other fellow developers

For the full interview: https://on.unity.com/3YCYRRy

post_text:
Pop quiz: What is a "spline" in the #gamedev context?

A spline is a type of path that is often used to build out rivers, roads, camera tracks, and other path-related features and tools. The Splines package, a new solution in #Unity 2022.2 Tech Stream, helps you create and use splines in your project.

Learn more üîΩ üîΩ

Take a look at all the new updates, now available in #Unity 2022.2 Tech Stream üîΩ üîΩ

post_text:
We‚Äôre at the end of our Games Focus series for 2022. We hope these blog posts give you more insight into how we‚Äôre delivering the tools and features you need to create games of all kinds and reach your players.

Ralph Hauwert, who oversees the development of our game engine and Editor, shares some of his personal highlights in the recap blog below ‚è¨

How can you make your games more accessible for everyone, especially in #VR? In our Creator Spotlight series, the Owlchemy Labs team, behind the game Cosmonious High, gave us some accessible game design tips and insight:

üé® For color blindness accessibility, they added different facets to some of the puzzles. In a mini-game where the player matches crystals of the same color, they also have a distinct pattern and shape so anyone can complete it.

üí° ‚ÄúDesign for one, extend to many‚Äù. When you create something accessible for one person, it‚Äôll likely benefit more people than you had in mind. For example, empowering one-handed players by making the second controller optional, also meant anyone could play while holding a snack, a drink, or even if one of the controllers was out of battery!

Find more insights in our new blog about accessibility in VR: https://on.unity.com/3HgetUT

post_text:
üëÄ Curious about updates to DOTS, render pipelines, Editor tooling, and platform support, coming soon in #Unity 2022.2 Tech Stream?

üì¢ Join us this Wednesday on Twitch (twitch.tv/unitytech) as we dive into these tools and features with devs behind the tech.

It‚Äôs time for another ‚ú®Made with Unity Roundup blog ‚ú®

Over the month of November, we were lucky to see some amazing creativity shown by our community. You‚Äôll find all the weekly projects we‚Äôve highlighted on our social media channels gathered in one blog and many tips to use in your projects from our latest dev takeover!

This month was also eventful with several Made with Unity games nominated for The Game Awards üëè

Read on for more details and everything Unity this past month üëá

Want to learn more about DOTS directly from our internal devs?

Join the next Dev Blitz Day on December 8 from 7am to 7pm EST for an AMA-style Q&A in the Unity Forums, SubReddit, and Discord. Your questions will be answered by the team behind the tech!

Details: on.unity.com/3GSWUKd

üí° Did you know that UI can be used strategically to either set up or break the "fourth wall", which affects game storytelling and player experience?

Find out how to use the right UI for the right situations in our latest blog ‚¨áÔ∏è

In June, we put a call for beta users to try the new Plastic SCM web experience.

Today, we‚Äôre happy to report that we are opening this functionality to all Plastic SCM Cloud Edition users in the form of an open beta ‚ú®

This will let you quickly manage user access, review repo content, kick off and complete code reviews, and granularly monitor usage, all within the Unity Dashboard üí°

Read our blog for full details üëá

The ninth blog in our Games Focus series is about achieving expanded scale for ambitious games with ECS for Unity (Entity Component System), a highly anticipated product area üïπ

Hear from Isaac Seah, product manager with the DOTS team, sharing more about the upcoming release of ECS in Unity 2022.2 Tech Stream üëá

post_text:
Improving tools for better cross-functional team collaboration is one of our key product development areas. In the seventh installation of our Games Focus series, we‚Äôre highlighting what‚Äôs ready for you today and in the near future ‚öô

Read on to learn more from the team behind these tools.

Last week, we shared Part 1 of our latest ‚ÄúTech from the Trenches‚Äù blog, with some best practices for importing and setting up art assets in your project üîß

This time, using the same RTS prototype, we‚Äôll actually start using those assets in the game, while saving as much time as possible. We‚Äôll go through components setup, sharing data in unrelated Prefabs, and other scripting tips to help on your projects! ‚åö

Read more üëá

post_text:
üîé On many projects, there are several repetitive and error-prone tasks, especially when it comes to integrating new art assets.

‚öô In our latest ‚ÄúTech from the Trenches‚Äù blog, we‚Äôll go through a simple RTS-like prototype we‚Äôve created. We‚Äôll be progressively adding more units to the game, with Editor tips to improve the workflow, and save time.

We'll cover asset organization and automation, texture settings, and more üòÑ For example, you'll find an easy way to do channel packing by creating a special asset type that generates channel-packed texture!

Read more üëá
